{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.slf4j:slf4j-jdk14:1.8.0-beta0`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5942-fails-javac-compile-org.slf4j-slf4j-jdk14-1.8.0-beta0-bfcf63d3\n\nThe original failing stage was `compileTestJava`: the generated `1.8.0-beta0` tests still referenced `org.slf4j.impl.StaticMarkerBinder` and `org.slf4j.impl.StaticMDCBinder`, but those types are not present in SLF4J `1.8.0-beta0`, producing `package org.slf4j.impl does not exist` / `cannot find symbol` errors in `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-jdk14:1.8.0-beta0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T15-45-06-629362Z.log`. There is preserved follow-up work that deletes those two binder tests and adds `JULServiceProviderTest`; repeated reruns then pass with 3/3 tests successful in `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-jdk14:1.8.0-beta0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T15-51-26-080739Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-jdk14:1.8.0-beta0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T15-53-28-949456Z.log`.\n\nThe workflow still ended as a failure because the fix-generation run itself terminated before it finalized/published its result: `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-jdk14:1.8.0-beta0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-06-06T15-51-26-074627Z.log` ends with `errorMessage: \"terminated\"`, and `stats/org.slf4j/slf4j-jdk14/1.8.0-beta0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: \"failure\"`, `generated_loc: 0`, and no emitted test/metadata artifact. Dynamic-access coverage is still unavailable because `stats/org.slf4j/slf4j-jdk14/1.8.0-beta0/stats.json` was never produced, and `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-jdk14:1.8.0-beta0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` also shows the entry still lacks `metadata/org.slf4j/slf4j-jdk14/1.8.0-beta0/reachability-metadata.json`.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch and confirm that replacing the removed binder coverage with `JULServiceProviderTest` is the right adaptation for SLF4J `1.8.0-beta0`.\n2. If that test change is acceptable, add/regenerate `metadata/org.slf4j/slf4j-jdk14/1.8.0-beta0/reachability-metadata.json` and refresh stats for `org.slf4j:slf4j-jdk14:1.8.0-beta0`.\n3. Rerun the coordinate checks/tests after that refresh to confirm the javac failure is resolved and stats/coverage artifacts are produced."}}
